The paper deals with the design and implementation of a multi-antenna downlink transmission system, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also addresses technical challenges related to the practical implementation of the system, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The proposed algorithms for precoder design involve optimization techniques, which are related to machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG).
